HEADWORD: Waterish
<hw>Wa"ter*ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>w⟦ae⟧terisc</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Resembling water; thin;
watery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Feed upon such nice and <qex>waterish</qex> diet.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Somewhat watery; moist; <as>as, <ex>waterish</ex>
land</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterishness</ent>⟦br⟧
